My suggestions and comments:


LAN Requester: (not sure if to be mentioned here ...)
  -full support for all object settings for public/private apps definitions
  -logoff exit like profile.cmd for logon
  -Logon Startup folder (deleted on Logoff!)
  -real wps integration of that LAN server GUI
  -a simple GUI mechanism to REMOVE a certain resource assignment from multiple users !
   (assigning can be done via drag&drop of a bunch of users onto a resource)

VIO/Full-screen OS/2 & dos command line
  -if no program is running, close session without confirmation !
  -more than 102 scroll buffer (is a limit necessary ?)
  -ability to define font and size for each text session program object
   use default if not defined

General OS
>>>  PSG   -add true read/write VFAT.IFS
If the above statement is not already meaning this:
  -IFS driver to lock/unlock disk images for to be able to read/write directly
   Should support at least DSK image and XDF, better: also EMT and MIF and more ...

WPS:
  -full support for ALL object settings for public/private apps in settings notebooks
  -assoc type for build in file operations: e.g. for printing !
  -hide task list entry option for every object !
  -environment variables setable for every program icon supporting %substitution%.
   user can select between defining 1) within a MLE or 2) within an ascii-file
>>> this avoids having a batch file for PM progs which need special env settings
>>> that one does not want to set in config.sys ! So no more ugly vio windows
>>> for starting a pm prog (just hiding them is not enough !)
>>> Defining within an ascii-file would be great to share env settings via a file server !

>>>  PSG   -run detached option for icons in settings pages
YES !!!


>>> TM     -programs in the startup should run in foreground, not background
This should be selectable !!! Also run minimized/maximized ! In general:

>>>  MC    -templates represent object class, changes change class defaults
>>>         NOTE: this would satisfy ED's suggestion above RE: folder settings
  Above only for newly created instances! For existing instances:
  -settings scheme for to copy settings to existing objects like color scheme does it for colours

FileSystems
>>>  BS    -meaningful non-system disk message for OS/2-formatted floppies
  Better (?):
  -default boot sector that boots from harddisk if no system on floppy



