Well, as long as we're imagining....

1.  A process killer like WatchCat, only that works with PS/2-style mice :-)

2.  Improving Icon Editor so that it saves icons in 2.0 format by default,
not that this makes a lot of difference, but it's a confusing thing to the
casual user.

3.  Improving font installation by adopting something like FontFolder.  Why
do you have to "Edit" a font already installed in a palette in order to get
to the install routine?

4.  When E.exe detects null characters and the user selects "stop loading
file," then don't have E.exe open an Untitled document.  Stop loading E.exe,
too!

5.  Make dialog boxes have consistent button titles.  Why does PM-Checklist,
for example, make you push "Cancel" when it completes?  What's wrong with
"OK"?

6.  Ini file editors and utilities.

7.  Bundle "Extended Desktop" with the WPS.

